Vice President Mike Pence spoke at the Freitas Family Farm in Lemoore, California, emphasizing the importance of passing the United States-Mexico-Canada Agreement (USMCA). He stated that the agreement would create new jobs and increase agricultural exports. Pence also expressed optimism about the ongoing discussions with Speaker Pelosi and Democratic leaders in the House, stating that they were not far apart on the issues. He mentioned that addressing workforce issues in the city and on the farm would involve vocational education and training, as well as modernizing the immigration system to prioritize the needs of the American economy. Pence also addressed other topics, including the prosecution of Jeffrey Epstein, healthcare conditions for children at the border, and the recent California law granting undocumented immigrants access to healthcare.